title: For Sale:  WWII STAR MODEL B pistols
location: Mount Pleasant just west of Racine, Racine, Wisconsin
postcontent:
Looking to sell two (2) WWII Spanish Model B pistols chambered in 9mm Luger.  These are the older heavier built models.  I am told these have more machined parts and less stamped parts.  I also have the issued cleaning rods for both.   

I purchased them from AIM Surplus back when they still had them a few years ago. The guns fire well, but sometimes the empty shell fails to extract all of the way. Extractor issue I am guessing.  The guns have the wood grips and not the black plastic "synthetic" grips.  

I paid 800 for the pair and would like to get as close to that as possible.  Feel free to make an offer. Nobody under 21 please and must be legally able to own firearms. 

Here is the link to the AIM site 
http://www.aimsurplus.com/product.aspx?item=F3StarB

This is how AIM described them, "WWII Star Model B 9mm Luger Pistols. Manufactured in Spain between 1943-44 as part of a 15,000 piece contract for Bulgaria. These pistols feature original Wartime Factory Markings. They were refinished by the Russians after WWII as was common practice with firearms they obtained during & after the War. They will have checkered wood or black synthetic grips. Some markings may be lighter due to the refinishing. Almost identical design to the 1911. Includes 1-8rd magazine."

Would like to sell both to the same person/collector.  
Local pickup only.  I have 800.00 into them, but feel free to make an offer for both.

title: For Sale:  Bren MK 1
location: New York, New York, United States
postcontent:
The Bren LMG was developed from the ZB26, a Czech LMG designed at Brno, by the Royal Small Arms Factory at Enfield. The name was an amalgamation of BRno and ENfield.

Production began in 1937 at Enfield RSAF and it was accepted into service in 1938, when production also commenced at Inglis in Canada and Lithgow in Australia from 1940. Daimler and a corporation of manufacturs called Monotype also produced them. Others were made at the Small Arms Factory in India
The Bren became the centre of all section tactics during WW2, and had it's own transport in the form of the Universal (Bren) Carrier. It remained the standard section weapon long after the war and soldiered on into the 1980's rechambered and barrelled for 7.62 ammunition.

Set #2791/3000

Here's a little about the pistol from Chiappa's site:
Defense revolver, offers great concealability thanks to a very unusual profile. The flat cylinder grants maximum comfort. The new Chiappa Rhino barrel is aligned with the bottom most chamber which is the key component to Rhino's tame characteristics. The position of the barrel lowers the center of gravity and yields a centerline of the bore more in line with the shooter's arm allowing for the most natural "point ability" while engaging a target. This characteristic also drastically reduces both recoil and muzzle flip which insures subsequent shots to be on target faster than ever before. The reduction of the recoil allows for the use of ultra light alloys to be used in the construction of the Rhino minimizing any adverse effect. The flat sided cylinder design of the Rhino reduces the typical revolver profile allowing greater concealment. Featuring both double and single action characteristics, the single action is actuated by a hammer cocking device that engages the unexposed hammer to prepare to fire.

postcontent: This rifle was built by red hawk custom shop in Colorado. It is a Remington 700 action with a 26" bull barrel cambered in 7mm-08. The 7mm-08 is a cartridge born from the 308 necked down to .284. There are a few great advantages to this the bullets used will have a higher BC( ballistic coefficient ). Which means the bullet flies farther, straighter, truer, greater velocity, high energy, and less recoil. It is ballistically far superior to the .308. I was able to shoot 3/4 moa with un-tuned loads very easily this is a 1/2 moa gun at 100 yards easily. It is set in a bell and Carlson A5 completely adjustable stock comb height, length of pull, and cant. Red hawk also installed a badger ordinance enlarged bolt knob, a talley 20 moa picatinny scope mount, lapped the bolt lugs, and tuned the trigger. This action is slick has been well taken care has only had 200 down the pipe. It comes with 1lb of imr4350, 40 rds of ammo, a set of RCBS dies, and assorted bullets
